  "prompt": "What is the best medicine for allergies or a cold?",
  "response": "For allergies, antihistamines like Zyrtec, Claritin, or Allegra can help reduce symptoms. Nasal sprays like Flonase can also provide relief.\n\nFor colds, over-the-counter medications can help manage symptoms:\n- Decongestants like Sudafed for nasal congestion\n- Pain relievers like Tylenol or Advil for aches and fever\n- Cough suppressants like Robitussin\n- Throat lozenges for sore throat\n\nRest, hydration, and vitamin C can also help with both conditions. If symptoms persist or worsen, consult a healthcare professional.",
